# Motimot project standards

When editing this repo (Unity C# game, word-of-the-day), always follow these rules.

## Coding style (C#)

- **Namespaces:** `Motimot` for runtime code (`Assets/Scripts/Runtime/`), `Motimot.Editor` for editor-only code (`Assets/Scripts/Editor/`).
- **Naming:** PascalCase for types, public/protected members, constants; camelCase for private fields, parameters, locals. Interfaces: `I` prefix (e.g. `IWordProvider`).
- **Files:** One main type per file; filename = type name (e.g. `GameState.cs`).
- **Style:** 4 spaces, always use braces, prefer `sealed` and `readonly` where appropriate. Use [GAME_SPECIFICATION](docs/GAME_SPECIFICATION.md) nomenclature (hidden word, guess, tile, row, feedback, etc.).

Full details: **docs/CODING_STYLE_AND_ASSEMBLIES.md**.

## Assemblies

- **Motimot** (`Scripts/Runtime/Motimot.asmdef`): all game logic and runtime code.
- **Motimot.Editor** (`Scripts/Editor/Motimot.Editor.asmdef`): editor tools only; references `Motimot`. No UnityEditor code in Runtime.

## Commits

- **Message:** Short imperative subject (~50 chars); optional body. No tool/watermark attribution (e.g. no "Made with Cursor").
- **Command:** Use `git commit -F <file>` or `printf '%s' "message" | git commit -F -` so nothing is appended to the message.

